item.title: What's up with No-Ip?
item.dc:creator: @goneby1233 goneby1233
item.description:
@goneby1233 wrote:

Btw This MIGHT HELP

You might not have a router at all and like you said, it might be a bridge. So first let's find out if your computer is behind a router or not. To do this go to a command prompt and type ipconfig /all, and post all of the info here on the forum. Here are the steps to do this:

  1. Go to Start–>Run and type “cmd”

  2. A black command prompt screen will popup and you need to type “ipconfig /all” then press enter.

  3. The ipconfig command should display information about your network connections, go ahead and post that information in this thread.

  4. In order to post the information you need to right click and choose “select all”, then with the test highlighted you need to use the keyboard and press “ctrl + c” which is the keyboard shortcut command for copy. Then you can paste in the forum.

Let me know if you have any trouble doing this.

Just as an example mine looks like this:

Quote:

OR

Solution for users with multiple network adapters: Hl always automaticaly detect right IP address of network adapter that are connected in to internet, and force the game to use this adapter. This option should be turned off by hlpro.ini file. Edit the hlpro.ini file and in section [IL-2 Sturmovik (full version)] change value DetectLocalIP=1 to DetectLocalIP=0. Then open il2setup application and select right network adapter by network tab.

Solution for users with a software firewall:
The game using always UDP port 21000 (hyperlobby force this port). You must enable this port to both direction .Zonealarm offering only enable or disable acces to the internet and enable or disable listenning. Good is enable both when you want host games. Tiny Personal Firewall off
